list.abstract: full（英[fʊl]，美[fʊl]），英语单词，作形容词为满的；装满的；充满的。作副词为径直地；直接地；非常。作名词为盛期；顶点；整个。作动词为装满；使充满；把…打多褶以使…宽松。短语搭配有make full use of（充分利用）。例句为“An amazing story full of puzzles!（一个充满谜题的奇妙故事！）” full形容词类近义词有complete、filled等，副词类近义词有extremely、badly等，名词类近义词有integrity、entirety，相关反义词有wane、empty等。比较级为fuller。最高级为fullest。副词形式为fully，名词形式为fullness。

yingyinNormal.en: I've been feeling so lousy, you know, the last couple months . No job, no boyfriend. Well, at least my cup is half full. Half full of love.
yingyinNormal.zh: 过去两个月，我一直觉得好郁闷，没有工作，没有男友，至少现在我的杯子是半满了。半满的爱。

yingyinNormal.en: When we leave this room, you will no longer be dependents but full fledged members of our society. Faction before blood.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当我们离开这个房间，你们将不再嗷嗷待哺，而是成为我们这个社会中羽翼丰满的一员。派别高于血缘。

yingyinNormal.en: No, thank you. I have my hands full.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不用了，谢谢你，我太忙了。

yingyinNormal.en: I think we could go for full custody.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我看我们可以争取完全监护权。

yingyinNormal.en: Full cognitive recovery. We're ready.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这药能全面恢复认知力，我们准备好了。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《Rise of the Planet of the Apes》

yingyinNormal.en: Would you like some more, George? Full.
yingyinNormal.zh: 想要多来点吗，乔治？饱了。

yingyinNormal.en: 2 minutes. With the current at full power.
yingyinNormal.zh: 两分钟，在最佳情况下。

yingyinNormal.en: It's just, there is nothing. The city's full.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没房子了，纽约都住满了。

yingyinNormal.en: Anchor's away. Full sail. Aye, aye, Dog beard.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在起锚了。全速全进。遵命，狗船长！

yingyinNormal.en: There's a hole in the boat? It's full of holes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 船是不是有个洞？到处都是洞。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《大卫·贝克汉姆：探索未知之境》

yingyinNormal.en: Life jackets on. Aye, aye, Captain Dog. Full, sail.
yingyinNormal.zh: 穿上救生衣。穿上了，狗船长。出发！

yingyinNormal.en: You're full of surprises. Yes, like "My Fair Lady".
yingyinNormal.zh: 你真让人惊喜，对，就像“窈窕淑女”那样。

yingyinNormal.en: Mission, we're in full OMS burn, trying to back out.
yingyinNormal.zh: 控制中心，我们已开动最大马力，意图后退。

yingyinNormal.en: You're full of estrogen and you don't act like that.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你全身都是雌激素也没这样啊。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, the sailing boat does have an engine. Full sail.
yingyinNormal.zh: 哦，帆船上有引擎。全速前进！

yingyinNormal.en: How's the candy business? Sour? Nutty? Full of Nerds?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你糖果生意怎么样了？"酸"溜溜，疯颠颠[坚果]，宅男多[糖果品牌]吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Whatever. I bet all the full-size candy bars are gone.
yingyinNormal.zh: 随便，我敢说套装糖果肯定都发光了。

yingyinNormal.en: Well done, George! Would you like some more, George? Full.
yingyinNormal.zh: 做得好，乔治。想要多来点吗，乔治？饱了。

yingyinNormal.en: Well done, George! Would you like some more, George? Full.
yingyinNormal.zh: 做得好，乔治。想要多来点吗，乔治？饱了。

yingyinNormal.en: Because you're all full of that Texas "gee willikers" hooey.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为你满口德克萨斯口音啊。

examination_example.sentence: In contrast, suppose you give a reasonable argument: that <highlight>full</highlight>-time workers should not have to live in poverty.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相反，假设你给出一个合理的论点：全职工人不应该生活的很贫困。

examination_example.sentence: Many people who work part-time jobs actually want <highlight>full</highlight>-time jobs.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 许多做兼职工作的人实际上想要全职工作。

examination_example.sentence: These are people who may previously have felt the need to get a <highlight>full</highlight>-time job that provided insurance in order to cover themselves and their families.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些人以前可能觉得有必要找一份提供保险的全职工作，以便为自己和家人提供保险。

sense_info_list.en: containing or holding as much or as many as possible; having or containing a large number of sth.

examination_example.sentence: The web's <highlight>full</highlight> of articles offering tips on making time to read: "Give up TV" or "Carry a book with you at all times."
examination_example.sentence_trans: 网络上有很多文章提供了如何腾出时间阅读的建议：“放弃看电视”或“随身携带一本书”。

examination_example.sentence: The best lawyers made skyscrapers-<highlight>full</highlight> of money, tempting ever more students to pile into law schools.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 最好的律师赚得盆满钵满，吸引越来越多的学生涌入法学院。

examination_example.sentence: Similar to newly staked mining claims, they are <highlight>full</highlight> of potential.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 与新提出的采矿主张类似，它们充满了潜力。

examination_example.sentence: The possibility of <highlight>full</highlight> employment.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 充分就业的可能性。

examination_example.sentence: We still have a long way to go to get back to <highlight>full</highlight> employment, but at least we are now finally moving forward at a faster pace.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 要恢复充分就业，我们还有很长的路要走，但至少我们现在终于以更快的速度前进了。

examination_example.sentence: Because representative government presupposes an informed citizenry, the report supports <highlight>full</highlight> literacy.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 由于代议制政府以公民知情为前提，该报告支持全面识字。

examination_example.sentence: It doesn't then necessarily follow that one kind of reading is <highlight>fuller</highlight>, more advanced or more worthwhile than another.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这并不一定意味着一种阅读比另一种更充实、更高级或更有价值。

word_usage.usage:
“...对某人来说是合理的”用fair to/on sb. to do sth.表达。
示例：It's not fair on the students to keep changing the timetable.
不断改动时间表，这样对待学生不恰当。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 普通用词, 通常用于修饰单数或复数可数名词、不可数名词、物质名词、表示地点的专有名词, 放在冠词、指示代词、物主代词等之前, 而 whole 放在这些词之后。有时可与 whole, entire 和 total 换用。
强调事物在内容、程度、或数量方面已完整, 已达标准。
较正式用词, 只作定语, 一般只用于修饰单数名词(包括集合名词), 强调团体、时间段、数量等的整体, 含不能有所削减或增添之意, 用于修饰某一具体事物时常可与 whole 互换。
侧重指内容, 含有能包括所有的充足内容的意味。
侧重指未打折扣, 未除去成本或皮重等与净重、净数相对。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

derivative_info_list.mean: adv. 完全地；全部地；最大程度地；至少；整整；足足；详尽地；毫无遗漏地

word_family.mean: adj. 满的；装满的；充满的；完全的；完整的；丰满的；圆鼓鼓的；最高的；全神贯注于；充满…的

examination_example.sentence: Most gas cars can drive hundreds of miles on a <highlight>full</highlight> tank.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大多数汽油车加满油可以行驶数百英里。

examination_example.sentence: Beijing Opera is China's national opera and it is <highlight>full</highlight> of Chinese cultural traditions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 京剧是中国的国剧，充满了中国的文化传统。

examination_example.sentence: Our world is <highlight>full</highlight> of so many things to like!
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们的世界充满了很多值得喜欢的东西！

examination_example.sentence: It means that the robots built the <highlight>full</highlight> house in just 48 hours.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这意味着机器人在48小时内就建成了完整的房子。

examination_example.sentence: I give her <highlight>full</highlight> credit for making me the person who I am today.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我完全相信她使我成为今天的我。

examination_example.sentence: Soon enough, people asked her to make clothes, and it turned into a <highlight>full</highlight>-time business.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 很快，人们请她做衣服，这变成了她的一项全职工作。

examination_example.sentence: When your stomach feels <highlight>full</highlight>, stop eating.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当你的胃感到饱时，停止进食。

examination_example.sentence: A <highlight>full</highlight> stomach makes all the difference to a child's learning.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 吃饱肚子对孩子的学习有很大影响。

examination_example.sentence: Another thing is that it is very impolite to say you're <highlight>full</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 另一件事是说你吃饱了是非常不礼貌的。

examination_example.sentence: I didn't make <highlight>full</highlight> use of the time.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我没有充分利用时间。

examination_example.sentence: A banana plant grows to <highlight>full</highlight> height.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 香蕉树长得很高。

examination_example.sentence: Within a few weeks of <highlight>full</highlight> growth, the plant is done for the year.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在充分生长的几周内，植物就完成了全年的生长。

examination_example.sentence: Life will be difficult, but I have the confidence to live a happy, <highlight>full</highlight> life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 生活会很艰难，但我有信心过上幸福、充实的生活。

examination_example.sentence: The people in the past could live the lives to the <highlight>full</highlight> even without them.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 过去的人即使没有他们也能过上充实的生活。

examination_example.sentence: The vet has lived a <highlight>fullest</highlight> life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 兽医过着最充实的生活。

word_usage.usage:
“...对某人来说是合理的”用fair to/on sb. to do sth.表达。
示例：It's not fair on the students to keep changing the timetable.
不断改动时间表，这样对待学生不恰当。
